Research shows that older fathers increase the risk of schizophrenia due to mutations in sperm.
A study in France reveals alarming cannabis use statistics, prompting a government campaign to raise awareness of its harmful effects.
Breakthroughs in schizophrenia research link abnormal brain structure to impaired thought processes.
Genetic studies suggest a common ancestor for human genes a million years ago.
The Blue Brain Project aims to create a detailed model of the neocortex to simulate brain functions.
These advancements offer hope for understanding and treating complex brain disorders.
